RACE.RACE_TEXT: GRANTS PASS RACE 2 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 72. Claiming Purse 6500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE IN 2023. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $2,500 (Races at OR Fairs or WA Class C Tracks Not Considered in Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TEASPOON OF PEPPER chased the leaders to the backstretch, offered a bid leaving the three eighths along the rail, swung out for room into the stretch and rallied smartly to win going away. GALWALKSINTOABAR contested the pace outside of HYPHY, inched away from that one briefly nearing the second turn then could not stall the winner but hung onto the place. HYPHY dueled from the rail, kept pressure on GALWALKSINTOABAR to the second turn then was outkicked through the drive. SWISS SCRIPT chased the pace three wide for a half mile then lacked the needed late response. GREAT CURVES was outside of SWISS SCRIPT and four wide while trailing then came up empty when roused. CAL'S GIRL tracked the leaders for three eighths then gave way.

ENTRY.NAME: Cal's Girl
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked pace, saved ground, gave way

RACE.RACE_TEXT: OTOBA Juvenile S. GRANTS PASS RACE 3 5F Dirt CR: 71. Stakes Purse 20000. FOR TWO YEAR OLDS REGISTERED OREGON BREDS. FREE nominations closed Sunday, September 24 with five and one supplementary nomination of $200 each by closing time of entries. $200 to pass the entry box. First preference to winners. Second preference by total earnings. Field will be limited to ten starters. Weight 125 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WHISKEYJACK stalked the pace early then raced to the front when TRES VITE bore out, edged away on the second turn and held driving. TRES VITE hustled to the front but bore out six wide into the backstretch, pressed the winner three wide to the stretch but did not threaten. ROJO PEQUENO chased the top two, advanced inside on the second turn and was making up a bit of ground late. SHOT OF BRANDY lugged out on the first turn, was corrected, settled to the second turn, was two wide to the stretch but lacked the needed late response. PASS THE CROWN was chasing to the three eighths then saved ground but also did not rally. LIL BIT OF HEAVEN bore out on the first turn and put in a dull effort.

ENTRY.COMMENT: lugged out 1st turn, settled, 2wide, no rally

RACE.RACE_TEXT: George Hurliman Memorial S. GRANTS PASS RACE 5 6F Dirt CR: 75. Stakes Purse 20000. FOR THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD REGISTERED OREGON BREDS. FREE nominations closed Sunday, September 24 with nine or by supplementary nomination of $200 each by closing time of entries. $200 to pass the entry box. Preference by total earnings in 2022-2023. F ield will be limited to ten starters. Three-Year-Olds 124 lbs.; Older 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CABALLERANGO never far back, bid two wide on the far turn, dueled into the stretch then battled gamely to prevail. RODEO ROSE broke out sharply, was corrected but had no speed, bid three wide to the stretch then closed steadily to grab the place. SKEESIX prompted the pace early, took over when NORTHERN BLEND bolted, responded to mid stretch then was bested late. CORAZON DE LUCIA had no speed, trailed to the second turn then saved ground to the stretch and closed a bit late. NORTHERN BLEND hustled to the front but bolted on the backstretch, was pulled up but crossed the wire. BEING A BOSS tracked the pace two wide then drifted out slightly on the second turn, clipped heels with RODEO ROSE, fell then was walked off. The stewards conducted an inquiry into the accident but made no change.

ENTRY.COMMENT: hustled to lead, bolted, pulled up, crossed wire
